# Vue and Quasar

## Single-file component block order

- In every **`.vue`** SFC, top-level blocks appear **only** in this order: **`<template>`** (markup), then **`<script>`** (or **`<script setup>`**), then **`<style>`** (one or more blocks). Do not place **`<script>`** or **`<style>`** above **`<template>`**, and do not put **`<style>`** between **`<template>`** and **`<script>`**. This applies to all Vue files in the repo (app, layouts, Storybook workspace).

## UI and framework

- Use Vue 3 **Composition API** (`<script setup>`) consistent with existing components.
- Prefer **Quasar** (`q-*`) components and spacing/typography patterns from sibling files in the same area.
- **Scrollable regions**: when a template root or wrapper is the element that **may show a vertical scrollbar** (overflow scroll/auto) and scrollbar presence can change with content, add the global class **`hasScrollbar`** so `scrollbar-gutter: stable` prevents layout shift. See [scrollbar.scss](../../src/css/globals/scrollbar.scss) and [project-scss.mdc](project-scss.mdc).
- Keep **user-visible copy** in repo-root **i18n/** â€” never hardcode prose strings in templates, `_data/` files, or scripts.
- For SFC translations, use template `$t('camelCaseKey.subKey')` directly; do **not** import `useI18n` only to call `t(...)`.
- All top-level i18n keys use **camelCase with a lowercase first letter** (e.g. `globalWindowButtons`, `dialogs`, `errorNotFound`). Sub-keys follow the same convention.
- To add new strings: place them in an `L_*.ts` locale file under the matching folder (`components/<bucket>/<ComponentName>/` where `<bucket>` is `globals`, `elements`, or `other` â€” not `foundation`, which is Storybook-only; or `dialogs/`, `pages/`, or `globalFunctionality/`), import it in `i18n/en-US/index.ts`, and assign it to a camelCase top-level key. Do not add hardcoded strings inline to `index.ts`. Uncategorised app-wide strings belong in `globalFunctionality/L_unsortedAppTexts.ts` under `globalFunctionality.unsortedAppTexts`.
- In TypeScript scripts and Pinia stores (outside Vue templates), import `{ i18n } from 'app/i18n/externalFileLoader'` and call `i18n.global.t('camelCaseKey.subKey')`.
- **Electron global shortcuts**: app-wide **`keydown`** dispatch is registered from **`MainLayout.vue`** (after **`S_FaKeybinds`** loads); definitions and matching live under **`src/scripts/keybinds/`**. Adding commands: [fantasia-keybinds skill](../skills/fantasia-keybinds/SKILL.md) and [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) **Global keyboard shortcuts (faKeybinds)**.
- Storybook mocks: import specific non-markdown `L_*` locale modules directly â€” never the full `en-US/index.ts` â€” and provide placeholder strings for `documents.*` keys. See [fantasia-i18n skill](../skills/fantasia-i18n/SKILL.md).

## After UI changes

- Run the **quality gate** â€” `yarn testbatch:verify` â€” unless debugging one step ([testing-terminal-isolation.mdc](testing-terminal-isolation.mdc)); add or update **Playwright** component tests where the project already tests similar UI (see [fantasia-testing](../skills/fantasia-testing/SKILL.md) skill).
- For Vue SFCs under **`src/components/**`**, **`src/layouts/**`**, and **`src/pages/**`**, keep Vitest parity: each feature **`.vue`** retains a matching **`_tests/<Name>.vitest.test.ts`** (1:1 **presence** baseline). **`.vue`** has **no** failing coverage threshold in CI; the **`unit-components`** report uses **watermarks** (~**60%** lower band)â€”review and extend tests when lines or statements sit **below ~60%** ([vitest-tests.mdc](vitest-tests.mdc)). **`src/components/foundation/**`** is excluded from **`unit-components`** coverage. Colocated **`scripts/*.ts`** must satisfy **100%** on all four v8 metrics when included in **`unit-components`** coverage. Layout and page tests live in **`src/layouts/**/_tests/`** and **`src/pages/**/_tests/`** beside canvas-only Storybook previews.
- When adding or editing Storybook stories for `src/components/**`, place `*.stories.ts` inside each component's `_tests/` subfolder (`src/components/**/_tests/*.stories.ts`), set **`meta.title`** to **`Components/<bucket>/<ComponentName>`** (bucket = **`dialogs`**, **`elements`**, **`foundation`**, **`globals`**, or **`other`** under **`src/components/`**), and keep Storybook support wiring in `.storybook-workspace/.storybook` aligned (Quasar, Pinia, i18n mocks). **`foundation/`** catalogues are Storybook-only; use **`tags: ['skip-visual']`** and **`parameters.docs.disable: true`** per [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md). Optional `src/layouts/**/_tests/*.stories.ts` and `src/pages/**/_tests/*.stories.ts` are **canvas-only** (no Docs/autodocs); see [storybook-stories.mdc](storybook-stories.mdc).
- Storybook i18n note: avoid importing full locale roots (`i18n/index.ts`, `i18n/en-US/index.ts`) inside Storybook mocks/helpers because markdown document imports (`documents/*.md`) can fail Vite import analysis; import specific non-markdown `L_*` locale modules instead and use placeholder strings for document keys.

## `<script setup>` â€” documentation and size

- Add a short **JSDoc block** above each significant function (`/** ... */`), as in [GlobalWindowButtons.vue](src/components/globals/GlobalWindowButtons/GlobalWindowButtons.vue).
- Keep types strict in `<script setup lang="ts">`: avoid `any`; prefer explicit interfaces, generics, unions, `unknown`, or utility types.

### When the script section grows

1. **Structured production data** (menus, button sets, large config-shaped objects the app ships): colocate under the feature in a **`_data/`** folder (e.g. [globals/AppControlMenus/_data](src/components/globals/AppControlMenus/_data/)) and import into the SFC.
   - **Split big blobs across several TS files** inside `_data/` (one concern or surface per file â€” name files by what they define, e.g. `project.ts`, `tools.ts`, `buttons.ts`). A single â€śaggregatorâ€ť file that re-exports or composes smaller pieces is fine when it keeps the SFCâ€™s imports simple.
   - **`_data/` modules are normal TypeScript**: they may call **`i18n.global.t('...')`** (or your existing locale loader pattern), import shared helpers from **`src/scripts/`**, and attach **functions** (e.g. menu `trigger` callbacks) where the shape requires dynamic behavior. Keep user-visible strings in repo-root **`i18n/`** via keys, not hardcoded prose, unless the project already uses a local exception for that spot.
   - **Vitest fixtures** do **not** belong in `_data/` â€” keep them **inside** `*.vitest.test.ts` only (see [vitest-tests.mdc](vitest-tests.mdc)). **Component-testing** props for isolated SFCs should be supplied via **`COMPONENT_PROPS`** from Playwright (inline payloads in each `*.playwright.test.ts`). **Embedded** component-mode-only data that a parent SFC must own (e.g. a menu injected only when `TEST_ENV === 'components'`) may live as a **`const` in that `.vue` file** â€” not in a `_tests/*.ts` fixture module â€” see [playwright-tests.mdc](playwright-tests.mdc).
   - **Do not add dedicated tests whose only SUT is a `_data/` file**; cover production `_data` through `.vue` or other consumers.
2. **Pure, reusable helpers** (no Vue instance, no template-specific state): move to **`src/scripts/<feature>/`** and follow [typescript-scripts.mdc](typescript-scripts.mdc) (JSDoc; **group related functions** in the same module until **200 lines** or **50 lines per function** force a split â€” do **not** default to one tiny file per helper).
3. **Composable-style or feature-specific logic**: keep modules under `src/scripts/<feature>/` (or next to the feature when that matches existing patterns); keep each file to **one domain concern** with **several cohesive exports**, and avoid unrelated exports in one file.
4. **SFC and function size** â€” Follow [code-size-decomposition.mdc](code-size-decomposition.mdc): keep each **`.vue` at or under 250 lines**, each **function at or under 50 lines**, and avoid **TypeScript modules over 200 lines** (exemptions listed there). When limits force a split, place feature-owned logic **only** under **`src/components/<bucket>/<Feature>/scripts/`** (one or more `.ts` files) and/or add **subcomponents** in the same feature folder â€” **not** loose `.ts` beside the `.vue` at the feature root. Buckets are **`dialogs/`**, **`globals/`**, **`elements/`**, **`foundation/`**, **`other/`** (see [README](../../README.md)). External `<style>` files are a **last resort** and require **explicit user approval** before use. This `scripts/` folder is **not** a substitute for **`_data/`** (structured production payloads) or **`src/scripts/`** (shared app-wide helpers).
   - **How many `scripts/*.ts` files:** prefer **fewer, larger modules** that group a whole concern (table + rows + columns, dialog wiring + suspend, capture pipeline + API shape) until a file nears **200 lines** or a function nears **50 lines**; **avoid** a large set of **10â€“20 line** files that only split for splittingâ€™s sake. Same policy as [code-size-decomposition.mdc](code-size-decomposition.mdc) **Module count: prefer logical grouping**. Colocated **`scripts/_tests/*.vitest.test.ts`** can be consolidated when the production modules merge.

